data.title: About: Chashin, Hamadan
data.meta_description: Chashin (Persian: چشين, also Romanized as Chashīn and Cheshīn; also known as Kāshī, Kāshin, and Keshīn) is a village in Abaru Rural District, in the Central District of Hamadan County, Hamadan Province, Iran. At the 2006 census, its population was 1,447, in 360 families.
